107  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto absolutePos() const noexcept -> size_type {
108  return static_cast<size_t>(pos);

111  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void setPos(size_t new_pos) noexcept
112  {
113  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(new_pos >= 0 && new_pos <= static_cast<size_t>(mgr->d_size), "wrong iterator position");
114 
115  size_type front_size = static_cast<size_t>(mgr->d_buckets.front()->size);
116  size_type bindex = (new_pos + (static_cast<size_t>(mgr->d_bucket_size) - front_size)) >> static_cast<size_t>(mgr->d_bucket_size_bits);
117  size_type index_in_bucket = (new_pos - (new_pos < (front_size) ? 0 : front_size)) & static_cast<size_t>(mgr->d_bucket_size1);
118 
119  bucket = mgr->d_buckets.data() + bindex;
120 
121  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(bindex == mgr->d_buckets.size())) {
122  // end iterator
123  ptr = begin_ptr = first_stop = 0;
124  }
125  else {
126 
127  ptr = static_cast<cbuffer_pos>(&(*bucket)->at(static_cast<cbuffer_pos>(index_in_bucket)) - (*bucket)->buffer());
128  begin_ptr = (*bucket)->begin_index();
129  first_stop = (ptr < begin_ptr) ? (*bucket)->second_stop() : (*bucket)->first_stop();
130  }
131  pos = static_cast<difference_type>(new_pos);
132  }

134  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void offset(difference_type diff) noexcept
135  {
136  setPos(static_cast<size_t>(pos + diff));
137  }
138  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void go_next() noexcept
139  {
140  const cbuffer_pos sstop = (*bucket)->second_stop();
141  if (first_stop == sstop)
142  {
143  bucket++;
144  if (pos != static_cast<difference_type>(mgr->size())) {
145  begin_ptr = ptr = (*bucket)->begin_index();
146  first_stop = (*bucket)->first_stop();
147  }
148  else
149  ptr = begin_ptr = first_stop = 0;
150  }
151  else {
152  first_stop = sstop;
153  ptr = 0;
154  }
155  }
156  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void go_prev() noexcept
157  {
158  if (ptr == begin_ptr - 1)
159  {
160  bucket--;
161  ptr = static_cast<cbuffer_pos>((*bucket)->last_ptr() - (*bucket)->buffer());
162  begin_ptr = (*bucket)->begin_index();
163  first_stop = (*bucket)->second_stop();
164  }
165  else if (ptr == -1) {
166  first_stop = (*bucket)->first_stop();
167  ptr = (*bucket)->max_size1;
168  }
169  }

171  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator++() noexcept -> deque_const_iterator&
172  {
173  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(pos < static_cast<difference_type>(mgr->d_size), "increment iterator already at the end");
174  ++ptr;
175  ++pos;
176  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(ptr == first_stop )) {
177  go_next();
178  }
179  return *this;
180  }
181  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator++(int) noexcept -> deque_const_iterator {
182  deque_const_iterator _Tmp = *this;
183  ++(*this);
184  return _Tmp;
185  }
186 
187  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator--() noexcept -> deque_const_iterator& {
188  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(pos > 0, "increment iterator already at the end");
189  --ptr;
190  --pos;
191  if(SEQ_UNLIKELY(ptr < begin_ptr )) {
192  go_prev();
193  }
194  return *this;
195  }
196  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator--(int) noexcept -> deque_const_iterator {
197  deque_const_iterator _Tmp = *this;
198  --(*this);
199  return _Tmp;
200  }
201  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator*() const noexcept -> reference {
202  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(pos >= 0 && pos < static_cast<difference_type>(mgr->d_size), "dereference invalid iterator");
203  return (*bucket)->buffer()[ptr];
204  }
205  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator->() const noexcept -> pointer {
206  return std::pointer_traits<pointer>::pointer_to(**this);
207  }
208  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator+=(difference_type diff) noexcept -> deque_const_iterator& {
209  offset(diff);
210  return *this;
211  }
212  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator-=(difference_type diff) noexcept -> deque_const_iterator& {
213  offset(-diff);
214  return *this;
215  }

337  struct tvector_ra_iterator

340  using iterator_category = std::random_access_iterator_tag;
341  using value_type = typename BucketMgr::value_type;
342  using difference_type = typename BucketMgr::difference_type;
343  using pointer = typename BucketMgr::pointer;

352  tvector_ra_iterator() noexcept {}
353  tvector_ra_iterator(const BucketMgr* d) noexcept //begin
354  :data(const_cast<BucketMgr*>(d)), node(const_cast<chunk_type*>(d->d_buckets.data())), pos(0){}
355  tvector_ra_iterator(const BucketMgr* d, size_t) noexcept //end
356  :data(const_cast<BucketMgr*>(d)){
357  if (data->d_buckets.back().bucket->size == data->d_bucket_size) {
358  node = data->d_buckets.data() + data->d_buckets.size();
359  pos = 0;
360  }
361  else {
362  node = data->d_buckets.data() + data->d_buckets.size() - 1;
363  pos = data->d_buckets.back().bucket->size;
364  }
365  }
366 
367  auto computeAbsolutePos() const noexcept -> difference_type {
368  return ((node - data->d_buckets.data()) << data->d_bucket_size_bits) + pos;
369  }
370  void add(difference_type diff) noexcept{
371  difference_type abs = computeAbsolutePos();
372  abs += diff;
373  this->node = data->d_buckets.data() + (abs >> data->d_bucket_size_bits);
374  this->pos = static_cast<int>(abs & data->d_bucket_size1);
375  }
376  auto operator*() noexcept -> reference {
377  return node->bucket->buffer()[pos];
378  }
379  auto operator->() noexcept -> pointer {
380  return std::pointer_traits<pointer>::pointer_to(**this);
381  }
382  auto operator++() noexcept -> tvector_ra_iterator& {
383  ++pos;
384  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(pos >= data->d_bucket_size)) {
385  ++node;
386  pos = 0;
387  }
388  return *this;
389  }
390  auto operator++(int) noexcept -> tvector_ra_iterator {
391  tvector_ra_iterator _Tmp = *this;
392  ++(*this);
393  return _Tmp;
394  }
395  auto operator--() noexcept -> tvector_ra_iterator& {
396  --pos;
397  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(pos < 0)) {
398  --node;
399  pos = data->d_bucket_size1;
400  }
401  return*this;
402  }
403  auto operator--(int) noexcept -> tvector_ra_iterator {
404  tvector_ra_iterator _Tmp = *this;
405  --(*this);
406  return _Tmp;
407  }
408  auto operator+=(difference_type diff) noexcept -> tvector_ra_iterator& {
409  add( diff);
410  return *this;
411  }
412  auto operator-=(difference_type diff) noexcept -> tvector_ra_iterator& {
413  add(-diff);
414  return *this;
415  }
416  bool operator==(const tvector_ra_iterator& other) const noexcept { return node == other.node && pos == other.pos; }
417  bool operator!=(const tvector_ra_iterator& other) const noexcept { return node != other.node || pos != other.pos; }
418  bool operator<(const tvector_ra_iterator& other) const noexcept { return node < other.node || (node == other.node && pos < other.pos); }
419  bool operator>(const tvector_ra_iterator& other) const noexcept { return node > other.node || (node == other.node && pos > other.pos); }
420  bool operator<=(const tvector_ra_iterator& other) const noexcept { return !(*this > other); }
421  bool operator>=(const tvector_ra_iterator& other) const noexcept { return !(other > *this); }
422  auto operator+(difference_type diff) const noexcept -> tvector_ra_iterator {
423  tvector_ra_iterator tmp = *this;

431  }
432  auto operator-(const tvector_ra_iterator& other) const noexcept -> difference_type {
433  return ((node - other.node) << data->d_bucket_size_bits) + (pos - other.pos);

460  // Circular buffer class used internally by tiered_vector
461  // Actuall data are located in the same memory block and starts at start_data_T
462  template<class T, class Allocator>
463  struct CircularBuffer : BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>
464  {
465  static constexpr size_t size_BCB = sizeof(BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>);
466  // Start position for actual data in bytes
467  static constexpr size_t start_data_T = (size_BCB > sizeof(T)) ?
468  (size_BCB / sizeof(T) + ((size_BCB % sizeof(T)) != 0u ? 1 : 0)) :
469  1;
470  static constexpr size_t start_data = start_data_T * sizeof(T);
471  static constexpr bool relocatable = is_relocatable<T>::value && (sizeof(T) >= sizeof(size_t));
472 
473  using BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>::size;
474  using BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>::max_size1;
475  using BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>::max_size_;
476  using BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>::begin;
477 
478  // Initialize from a maximum size
479  CircularBuffer(cbuffer_pos max_size) noexcept
480  :BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>(max_size) {
481  //initialize empty buffer
482  }
483  // Initialize from a maximum size and a default value.
484  // This will set the buffer size to its maximum.
485  CircularBuffer(cbuffer_pos max_size, const T& val, Allocator& /*unused*/)
486  :BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>(max_size) {
487  size = max_size;
488  //initialize full buffer
489  cbuffer_pos i = 0;
490  try {
491  for (; i < max_size; ++i)
492  construct_ptr(buffer() + i, val);
493  }
494  catch (...) {
495  for (cbuffer_pos j = 0; j < i; ++j)
496  destroy_ptr(buffer() + j);
497  size = 0;
498  throw;
499  }
500  }
501 
502  // Destroy all values within buffer
503  void destroy(Allocator& /*unused*/) noexcept {
504  if (!std::is_trivially_destructible<T>::value) {
505  for (cbuffer_pos i = 0; i < size; ++i)
506  destroy_ptr(&(*this)[i]);
507  }
508  }
509 
510  //Disable copy
511  CircularBuffer(const CircularBuffer& other) = delete;
512  auto operator=(const CircularBuffer& other) -> CircularBuffer& = delete;
513 
514  //Raw buffer access
515  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto buffer() noexcept -> T* { return reinterpret_cast<T*>(reinterpret_cast<char*>(this) + start_data); }
516  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto buffer() const noexcept -> const T* { return reinterpret_cast<const T*>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(this) + start_data); }
517 
518  //Pointer on the first data
519  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto begin_ptr() noexcept -> T* { return buffer() + ((begin)&max_size1); }
520  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto begin_ptr() const noexcept -> const T* { return buffer() + ((begin)&max_size1); }
521  //Pointer on the last data
522  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto last_ptr() noexcept -> T* { return (buffer() + ((begin + size - 1) & max_size1)); }
523  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto last_ptr() const noexcept -> const T* { return (buffer() + ((begin + size - 1) & max_size1)); }
524  //Index of the first data
525  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto begin_index() const noexcept -> cbuffer_pos { return (begin)&max_size1; }
526  // Index of the first stop (either at size or max size)
527  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto first_stop() const noexcept -> cbuffer_pos {
528  cbuffer_pos p = begin_index();
529  return (p + size) > max_size() ? (max_size()) : (p + size);
530  }
531  // Index of the second stop (either at size or max size)
532  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto second_stop() const noexcept -> cbuffer_pos {
533  cbuffer_pos p = begin_index();
534  return (p + size) > max_size() ? (((p + size) & max_size1)) : (p + size);
535  }
536  //Buffer maximum size
537  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto max_size() const noexcept -> cbuffer_pos {
538  return max_size_;
539  }
540  //Check if full
541  auto isFull() const noexcept -> bool { return size == max_size(); }
542  //Element access.
543  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator[](cbuffer_pos index) noexcept -> T& {
544  //SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(index >= 0, "Invalid index");
545  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(!(index >= max_size() && begin == 0), "Invalid index");
546  return buffer()[(begin == 0) ? index : ((begin + index) & (max_size1))];
547  }
548  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto operator[](cbuffer_pos index) const noexcept -> const T& {
549  //SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(index >= 0, "Invalid index");
550  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(!(index >= max_size() && begin == 0), "Invalid index");
551  return buffer()[(begin == 0) ? index : ((begin + index) & (max_size1))];
552  }
553  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto at(cbuffer_pos index) noexcept -> T& {
554  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(index >= 0, "Invalid index");
555  return buffer()[((begin + index) & (max_size1))];
556  }
557  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto at(cbuffer_pos index) const noexcept -> const T& {
558  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(index >= 0, "Invalid index");
559  return buffer()[((begin + index) & (max_size1))];
560  }

562  // Front/back access
563  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto front() noexcept -> T& { return buffer()[begin]; }
564  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto front() const noexcept -> const T& { return buffer()[begin]; }
565  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto back() noexcept -> T& { return (*this)[size - 1]; }
566  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto back() const noexcept -> const T& { return (*this)[size - 1]; }

569  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void init_front() noexcept {
570  //init members for front buffer

574  // Resize buffer
575  void resize(cbuffer_pos s, Allocator& /*unused*/) {
576  if (s < size) {
577  if (!std::is_trivially_destructible<T>::value) {
578  for (cbuffer_pos i = s; i < size; ++i)
579  destroy_ptr(&(*this)[i]);
580  }
581  }
582  else if (s > size) {
583  cbuffer_pos i = size;
584  // Make sure to destroy constructed values in case of exception
585  try {
586  for (; i < s; ++i)
587  construct_ptr(&(*this)[i]);
588  }
589  catch (...) {
590  for (cbuffer_pos j = size; j < i; ++j)
591  destroy_ptr(&(*this)[j]);
592  throw;
593  }
594  }
595  size = s;
596  }
597  void resize(cbuffer_pos s, const T& value, Allocator& /*unused*/) {
598  if (s < size) {
599  if (!std::is_trivially_destructible<T>::value) {
600  for (cbuffer_pos i = s; i < size; ++i)
601  destroy_ptr(&at(i));
602  }
603  }
604  else if (s > size) {
605  cbuffer_pos i = size;
606  // Make sure to destroy constructed values in case of exception
607  try {
608  for (; i < s; ++i)
609  construct_ptr(&at(i), value);
610  }
611  catch (...) {
612  for (cbuffer_pos j = size; j < i; ++j)
613  destroy_ptr(&at(j));
614  throw;
615  }
616  }
617  size = s;
618  }

861  // Insert value at given position. Only works if the buffer is not full.
862  template <class... Args>
863  auto emplace(Allocator& allocator, cbuffer_pos pos, Args&&... args) -> T*
864  {
865  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(size != max_size_, "cannot insert in a full circular buffer");
866  if (pos > size / 2) {
867  move_right(allocator, pos);
868  }
869  else {
870  move_left(allocator, pos);
871  }
872 
873  T* res = &(*this)[pos];
874  if (relocatable) {
875  try {
876  construct_ptr(res, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
877  }
878  catch (...) {
879  //No choice but to destroy all values after pos and reduce the size in order to leave the buffer in a valid state
880  for (int i = pos + 1; i < size; ++i)
881  destroy_ptr(&(*this)[i]);
882  size = pos;
883  throw;
884  }
885  }
886  else {
887  // For non relocatable types, use move assignment to provide basic exception guarantee
888  *res = T(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
889  }
890 
891  return res;
892  }

1162  // Structure used to find the bucket size for a given tiered_vector size
1163  template<class T>
1164  struct FindBucketSize
1165  {
1166  auto operator() (size_t size, cbuffer_pos MinBSize, cbuffer_pos MaxBSize) const noexcept -> cbuffer_pos {
1167  cbuffer_pos res;
1168  if (size < static_cast<size_t>(MinBSize))
1169  res = static_cast<cbuffer_pos>(MinBSize);
1170  else {
1171  if (size < 4096) {
1172  if (size < 8) res = 2;
1173  else if (size < 32) res = 4;
1174  else if (size < 128) res = 8;
1175  else if (size < 512) res = 16;
1176  else if (size < 1024) res = 32;
1177  else if (size < 2048) res = 64;
1178  else res = 128;
1179  }
1180  else {
1181  // For now, select bigger chunk size as moving objects inside is faster than moving objects between chunks
1182  //unsigned bits = (bit_scan_reverse(size) >> 1) + 2;// log2 / 2 +2
1183  //res = static_cast<cbuffer_pos>(std::max(MinBSize, std::min(MaxBSize, static_cast<cbuffer_pos>(1U << bits))));
1184 
1185  // for sizeof(T) == 16*8, 1 is better
1186  // for sizeof(T) == 32, 2 is better
1187  // for sizeof(T) == 8 or 16, 3 is better
1188 
1189  static constexpr unsigned offset = sizeof(T) <= 16 ? 3 : (sizeof(T) <= 64 ? 2 : 1);
1190  unsigned bits = bit_scan_reverse(static_cast<size_t>(std::sqrt(size))) + offset;
1191  res = static_cast<cbuffer_pos>(1U << bits);
1192  }
1193  res = static_cast<cbuffer_pos>(std::max(MinBSize, std::min(MaxBSize, res)));
1194  }
1195  //std::cout << size << ": " << res << " ("<< MinBSize<<","<< MaxBSize<<")"<<std::endl;
1196  return res;
1197  }

1441  this->remove_back_bucket();
1442  throw;
1443  }

1445  pos += copied;

1455  current->grow_front(static_cast<cbuffer_pos>(copied));
1456  }
1457  }
1458  }
1459 
1460  // Update back values if necessary
1461  update_all_back_values();
1462 
1463  }

1643  // For each function, faster than using iterators
1644  template<class Functor>
1645  auto for_each(size_type start, size_type end, Functor fun) const -> Functor
1646  {
1647  size_type remaining = end - start;
1648  size_type bindex = bucket_index(start);
1649  size_type pos = static_cast<size_type>(bucket_pos(start));
1650 
1651  while (remaining) {
1652  const BucketType* cur = d_buckets[bindex].bucket;
1653 
1654  size_type offset = static_cast<size_t>(cur->begin) + pos;
1655  const T* b_end = cur->buffer() + cur->max_size();
1656  const T* _start = cur->buffer() + offset;
1657  if (_start > b_end)
1658  _start = cur->buffer() + (_start - b_end);
1659  size_type to_copy = std::min(remaining, static_cast<size_type>(cur->size) - pos );
1660  const T* _send = _start + to_copy;
1661  const T* _end = (_send > b_end) ? b_end : _send;
1662  while (_start < _end)
1663  fun(*_start++);
1664 
1665  if (_send > b_end) {
1666  _start = cur->buffer();
1667  _end = _start + to_copy - (static_cast<size_t>(cur->max_size()) - offset);
1668  while (_start < _end)
1669  fun(*_start++);
1670  }
1671  remaining -= to_copy;
1672  pos = 0;
1673  ++bindex;
1674  }
1675  return fun;
1676  }

1956  template< class... Args >
1957  auto insert_left(size_type pos, size_type bucket_index, int index, Args&&... args) -> T*
1958  {
1959  T* res = nullptr;
1960  //bucket is on the left side
1961  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(index == 0)) {
1962  --bucket_index; //we work on the previous bucket
1963  index = bucket(bucket_index)->size;
1964  }
1965  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(bucket(bucket_index)->size < d_bucket_size)) {
1966  //SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(bucket_index == 0, "Corrupted tiered_vector structure");
1967  // We insert into the first bucket which is not full
1968  // Might throw, fine
1969  res = bucket(bucket_index)->emplace(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1970  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bucket_index].update();
1971  }
1972  else if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(bucket_index == 0)) {
1973  //insert into full first bucket
1974  // Might throw, fine
1975  T tmp = std::move(d_buckets[0]->insert_pop_front(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...));
1976  try {
1977  res = create_front_bucket()->push_back(get_allocator(), std::move(tmp));
1978  }
1979  catch (...) {
1980  //check if front buffer is empty
1981  if (d_buckets[0]->size == 0)
1982  this->remove_front_bucket();
1983  throw;
1984  }
1985  if (StoreBackValues) {
1986  d_buckets[0].update();
1987  d_buckets[1].update();
1988  }
1989  }
1990  else {
1991  //we are going to loose value at index 0, save it
1992  size_t bindex = bucket_index;
1993  //T tmp = std::move((*bucket(bindex))[0]);
1994  //bucket(bucket_index)->insert<false>(index, value);
1995 
1996  // Might throw, fine
1997  T tmp = std::move(bucket(bucket_index)->insert_pop_front(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...));
1998  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bucket_index].update();
1999 
2000  //propagate down to left side
2001  while (--bindex > 0) {
2002  // Might throw, fine
2003  if (BucketType::relocatable)
2004  bucket(bindex)->push_back_pop_front_relocatable(tmp);
2005  else
2006  tmp = std::move(bucket(bindex)->push_back_pop_front(std::move(tmp)));
2007  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bindex].update();
2008  }
2009  //first bucket
2010  BucketType* bucket = d_buckets.front().bucket;
2011  if (!bucket->isFull()) {
2012  // Might throw, fine
2013  bucket->push_back(get_allocator(), std::move(tmp));
2014  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[0].update();
2015  }
2016  else {
2017  if (BucketType::relocatable)
2018  bucket->push_back_pop_front_relocatable(tmp);
2019  else
2020  tmp = std::move(bucket->push_back_pop_front(std::move(tmp)));
2021  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[0].update();
2022  bucket = create_front_bucket();
2023  try {
2024  bucket->push_back(get_allocator(), std::move(tmp));
2025  }
2026  catch (...) {
2027  //remove front buffer
2028  this->remove_front_bucket();
2029  throw;
2030  }
2031  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[0].update();
2032  }
2033  res = &at(pos);
2034  }
2035  return res;
2036  }
2037  template< class... Args >
2038  auto insert_right(size_type pos, size_type bucket_index, int index, Args&&... args) -> T*
2039  {
2040  T* res = nullptr;
2041  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(bucket(bucket_index)->size < d_bucket_size)) {
2042  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(bucket_index == 0 || bucket_index == d_buckets.size() - 1, "Corrupted tiered_vector structure");
2043  // Might throw, fine
2044  res = bucket(bucket_index)->emplace(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
2045  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bucket_index].update();
2046 
2047  }
2048  else if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(bucket_index == d_buckets.size() - 1)) {
2049  // Inserting into last (full) bucket
2050  // Might throw, fine
2051  T tmp = std::move(bucket(bucket_index)->insert_pop_back(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...));
2052  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bucket_index].update();
2053  try {
2054  res = create_back_bucket()->push_back(get_allocator(), std::move(tmp));
2055  }
2056  catch (...) {
2057  // Remove empty back bucket
2058  if (d_buckets.back()->size == 0)
2059  remove_back_bucket();
2060  throw;
2061  }
2062  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets.back().update();
2063  }
2064  else {
2065 
2066  size_type bindex = bucket_index;
2067  // Might throw, fine
2068  T tmp = std::move(bucket(bindex)->insert_pop_back(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...));
2069  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bindex].update();
2070 
2071  // Propagate to right buckets with successive push_front
2072  while (++bindex < static_cast<size_type>(d_buckets.size() - 1)) {
2073  //Might throw, fine
2074  if (BucketType::relocatable)
2075  bucket(bindex)->push_front_pop_back_relocatable(tmp);
2076  else
2077  tmp = std::move(bucket(bindex)->push_front_pop_back(std::move(tmp)));
2078  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bindex].update();
2079  }
2080 
2081  //last bucket
2082  BucketType* bucket = d_buckets.back().bucket;
2083  if (!bucket->isFull()) {
2084  // Might throw, fine
2085  bucket->push_front(get_allocator(), std::move(tmp));
2086  //if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets.back().update();
2087  }
2088  else {
2089  // Might throw, fine
2090  if (BucketType::relocatable)
2091  bucket->push_front_pop_back_relocatable(tmp);
2092  else
2093  tmp = std::move(bucket->push_front_pop_back(std::move(tmp)));
2094  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets.back().update();
2095  bucket = create_back_bucket();
2096  bucket->push_front(get_allocator(), std::move(tmp));
2097  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets.back().update();
2098  }
2099  res = &at(pos);
2100  }
2101  return res;
2102  }

2269  void resize(size_type size)
2270  {
2271  if (size == d_size)
2272  return;
2273 
2274  if (size > d_size) {
2275  // Might throw, fine
2276  ensure_has_bucket();
2277 
2278  //add missing buckets
2279  size_type missing = static_cast<size_t>(size - d_size);
2280  size_type last_bucket_rem = static_cast<size_t>(bucket_size() - d_buckets.back()->size);
2281 
2282  if (missing < last_bucket_rem) {
2283  // The last bucket has enough space: just resize it
2284  // Might throw, the bucket remains in its original form, fine
2285  d_buckets.back()->resize(d_buckets.back()->size + static_cast<cbuffer_pos>(missing), get_allocator());
2286 
2287  d_size += missing;
2288  }
2289  else {
2290  // Resize last bucket
2291  // Might throw, the bucket remains in its original form, fine
2292  d_buckets.back()->resize(bucket_size(), get_allocator());
2293 
2294  missing -= last_bucket_rem;
2295  d_size += last_bucket_rem;
2296 
2297  size_type new_bucket_count = missing / static_cast<size_t>(bucket_size());
2298  int last_bucket_size = static_cast<int>(missing % static_cast<size_t>(bucket_size()));
2299 
2300  try {
2301  //add full buckets
2302  for (size_type i = 0; i < new_bucket_count; ++i) {
2303  BucketType* b = create_back_bucket();
2304  b->resize(bucket_size(), get_allocator());
2305  d_size += static_cast<size_t>(bucket_size());
2306 
2307  }
2308  //add last
2309  if (last_bucket_size) {

2827  template<class Iter, class Cat>
2828  void insert_cat(size_type pos, Iter first, Iter last, Cat /*unused*/) {
2829  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(pos <= size(), "invalid insert position");
2830  if (first == last)
2831  return;
2832 
2833  if (pos < size() / 2) {
2834  //push front values
2835  size_type prev_size = size();
2836  // Might throw, fine
2837  for (; first != last; ++first)
2838  push_front(*first);
2839 
2840  size_type num = size() - prev_size;
2841  // Might throw, fine
2842  std::reverse(begin(), begin() + num); // flip new stuff in place
2843  std::rotate(begin(), begin() + num, begin() + (num + pos));
2844  }
2845  else {
2846  // push back, might throw
2847  size_type prev_size = size();
2848  for (; first != last; ++first)
2849  push_back(*first);
2850  // Might throw, fine
2851  std::rotate(begin() + pos, begin() + prev_size, end());

3465  void erase(size_type first, size_type last)
3466  {
3467  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(first <= last, "erase: invalid positions");
3468  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(last <= size(), "erase: invalid last position");
3469  if (first == last) return;
3470  size_type space_before = first;
3471  size_type space_after = size() - last;
3472 
3473  if (space_before < space_after) {
3474  std::move_backward(begin(), begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(first), begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(last));
3475  resize_front(size() - static_cast<size_t>(last - first));
3476  }
3477  else {
3478  //std::move(begin() + last, end(), begin() + first);
3479  iterator it = begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(first);
3480  manager()->for_each(last, size(), [&](T& v) {*it = std::move(v); ++it; });
3481  resize(size() - static_cast<size_t>(last - first));
3482  }
3483  }
